      <hedline>
        <hl1>An Ugly Charge Of Anti-Semitism</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Menachem Petrushka letter comments on July 18 article on allegations of anti-Semitism against Hillary Rodham Clinton in book by Paul and Mary Fray (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your July 18 editorial defending Hillary Rodham Clinton against charges of anti-Semitism recalls that she actively worked for the impeachment of President Nixon.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Your July 18 editorial defending Hillary Rodham Clinton against charges of anti-Semitism recalls that she actively worked for the impeachment of President Nixon.</p>
        <p>Mr. Nixon may have disliked Jews intensely and often used anti-Semitic language, but when the chips were down he came through for Israel. He saved Israel from destruction in the 1973 war by supplying it with vast amounts of arms. Supporters of Israel are forever grateful.</p>
        <p>MENACHEM PETRUSHKA  Flushing, Queens, July 18, 2000</p>
      </block>
